{
  "stem": "10353.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And incidentally that little can or that little dish that they had, if they lost it or somebody stole it from 'em, then that was the finish.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And similarly if somebody got dysentery, that was also the finale.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And people were dying on daily basis.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it-- it was no longer-- you know, you didn't even pay too much attention.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You just piled them up like a stack of wood.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then the wagon that would come and pile them up, you know, just throw them out and take them into the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a common sight that happened twice daily, so it wasn't frightening.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, we were adjacent to the stalag that contained the Dutch Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were-- they were treated similarly to us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They also had their own clothes on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the-- [SIGHS] in March-- from-- in the last three weeks of March of 1944-- 1945, pardon me. 1945 was most crucial, because people were dropping dead by the-- by the lot, you know.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were dying and-- and you saw the wagon hauling away the corpses, you know, in-- in a more frequent [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] period.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Towards the end of March, I believe it was around March 27, 28, it was Pesach, I remember that, when we-- all of a sudden we were ordered that the younger people have to report to work to go and clean out some cisterns that were located near the kitchens, because they-- during the winter, they gathered an awful lot of grime and so on.",
      "word_count": 69
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were-- we were given the orders to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to pump out with the water from those cisterns and to clean out those basins.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
